  "prompt": "What are the abbreviations for degrees?",
  "response": "Here are common abbreviations for various academic degrees:\n\n**Associate Degrees:**\n- AA: Associate of Arts\n- AS: Associate of Science\n- AAS: Associate of Applied Science\n\n**Bachelor's Degrees:**\n- BA: Bachelor of Arts\n- BS: Bachelor of Science\n- BFA: Bachelor of Fine Arts\n- BBA: Bachelor of Business Administration\n- BEng: Bachelor of Engineering\n- BEd: Bachelor of Education\n- BSc (or SB): Bachelor of Science\n\n**Master's Degrees:**\n- MA: Master of Arts\n- MS (or MSc): Master of Science\n- MFA: Master of Fine Arts\n- MBA: Master of Business Administration\n- MEd: Master of Education\n- MEng: Master of Engineering\n- MPH: Master of Public Health\n- MPA: Master of Public Administration\n\n**Doctoral Degrees:**\n- PhD: Doctor of Philosophy\n- MD: Doctor of Medicine\n- JD: Juris Doctor (Doctor of Law)\n- EdD: Doctor of Education\n- DSc (or ScD): Doctor of Science\n- PsyD: Doctor of Psychology\n- DBA: Doctor of Business Administration\n\n**Honorary Degrees:**\n- LLD: Doctor of Laws (honorary)\n- LittD: Doctor of Letters (honorary)\n\nThese abbreviations can be appended to an individual's name to denote their academic qualifications.",
